1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:02,210
I'm sure when you
think about the future,

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:04,260
there's things that you're hoping for.

3
00:00:04,260 --> 00:00:06,470
There's things that you're planning to do,

4
00:00:06,470 --> 00:00:08,020
but maybe you're not quite sure

5
00:00:08,020 --> 00:00:11,310
how to express how you
feel about that in English.

6
00:00:11,310 --> 00:00:12,500
Well, in this English lesson,

7
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,110
I will teach you a whole bunch
of phrases that you can use

8
00:00:15,110 --> 00:00:17,470
to talk about things
that you're hoping for,

9
00:00:17,470 --> 00:00:18,800
goals that you have set,

10
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:21,515
and things that you are
planning to do in the future.

11
00:00:21,515 --> 00:00:24,182
(upbeat music)

12
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:28,370
Before we get this lesson started,

13
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:30,150
I should mention one thing.

14
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:32,302
I'm sure you already
know how to use phrases

15
00:00:32,302 --> 00:00:35,500
like I am going to, or I will,

16
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,870
to talk about things you are
going to do in the future.

17
00:00:38,870 --> 00:00:39,703
And in this lesson,

18
00:00:39,703 --> 00:00:42,880
I'm not going to help you
learn the future tenses.

19
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:45,670
Instead, I'm going to teach
you some other phrases

20
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:47,930
that English speakers commonly use

21
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:50,560
when they're talking about
things that they are going to do.

22
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:51,640
So stick around for that.

23
